'''Urumqi Foreign Economic Relations and Trade Fair''' ({{zh|c=<U+4E4C><U+9C81><U+6728><U+9F50><U+5BF9><U+5916><U+7ECF><U+6D4E><U+8D38><U+6613><U+6D3D><U+8C08><U+4F1A>}}), commonly abbreviated as '''Urumqi Fair''' ({{zh|c=<U+4E4C><U+6D3D><U+4F1A>}}), is an annual trade fair held in [[Urumqi]] of [[Xinjiang]], [[People's Republic of China|China]], since it was started on September 2, 1992.<ref>[http://www.aboutxinjiang.com/topic/node_52487.htm Aboutxinjiang-Topics-China Urumqi Foreign Economic Relations and Trade Fair]</ref> Its purpose is to promote trading and market exploration in [[Northwestern China]] with foreign countries mainly in [[Central Asia]]. Urumqi Fair is the largest trade fair in [[Western China]]. 

The 17th Urumqi Foreign Economic Relations and Trade Fair, the latest event, was held in September 2008. It is the first time that the fair seeing participants from the [[Ministry of Commerce of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Commerce]] and the [[China Council for Promotion of International Trade]].<ref>[http://www.cctv.com/program/bizchina/20080902/102963.shtml 17th Urumqi Trade Fair opens - CCTV International]</ref>

